    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-05-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-05-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="685"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d685">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/1617.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-05-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 4, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Among the foreign elements in the City of Mexico the anxiety is seemingly
                    increasing, due in part to fear that negotiations for peace will fail and
                    general anarchy obtain; and in part to popular resentment of supposed impending
                    intervention. Americans and the other colonies are probably concerting measures
                    of precaution. Americans seem to be generally well armed. Success of peace
                    negotiations would avert any immediate danger.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
